<div><h3>MKT 5401 - Marketing Research </h3>  <hr>This course examines the basic concepts and techniques used in marketing research as a problem-solving aid in decision making in marketing. Problem definition, research design, types of information and measurement scales, and evaluation and utilization of secondary data with emphasis on electronic access are discussed. Students are trained in the basic methods of primary data collection, including structured and unstructured interviews, focus groups and surveys. Practical and intensive applications on sample size, questionnaire design, data analyses and interpretation are emphasized, as well as discussion of advanced multivariate techniques for inputting and analyzing data using the SPSS statistical package.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=25&coid=82352" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=25&coid=82352&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=25&coid=82352&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt9781" target="_blank">MKT 4400</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>Â  OR STAT4600<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varies<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt9781"></div></div>		</td>
